> These warm, autumnal desserts are instant fall favorites. We send you two flavors of deliciously rich Bundt cakes topped with a sweet, buttery caramel sauce: pumpkin and apple cinnamon. The best part? We did all the hard work, so all you have to do is heat them up whenever you need a sweet treat.

Keep frozen or refrigerated until ready to eat; best if used within 7 days. If frozen, thaw in the refrigerator (at 40 degrees) overnight or at room temperature for ~{2-3%hours} before eating.

== Serving Suggestion ==

> RECOMMENDED: Remove plastic wrap from trays; microwave until warmed through, ~{50-60%seconds}. (Do not overheat.) Let cakes cool for ~{2%minutes}, then turn out onto plates and serve.

> OVEN ALTERNATIVE: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Remove plastic wrap from trays; place on a #baking sheet{} and bake until warmed through, ~{14-16%minutes}. (Note: Oven times may vary.) Let cakes cool for ~{2%minutes}, then turn out onto plates and serve.

Use @apple cider Bundt cake with caramel sauce{2%units} and @pumpkin spice Bundt cake with caramel sauce{2%units} for 4 servings total.